This is a very fun and clever article. I really like how things escalate all the way through, and it felt like you were really taking into account all the things modern people take for granted that would be affected by this anomaly (Eskobar's point notwithstanding).

Another thing I like - sometimes there's a trend in SCPs for things to  through a kind of magical thinking lens, where things are just a little too pat - if someone else had written this they might have put in glass beads instead of beetles. There's a lot of disparate and seemingly unrelated elements here (beetles? In alcohol? That attract sand?) but they're very simple, so it's very weird but easy to read and understand, and I actually really appreciate that the moving parts here kept me on my toes.





